          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were self-supporting calcium foils of",
                "about 1.0 mg/cm**2 and 0.1 mg/cm**2 thickness prepared",
                "by vacuum evaporation of calcium on Al(2)O(3) support",
                "foils of about 0.06 mg/cm**2 thickness.",
                "At the medium angles(Ang(lab)=20-28 degree) a thin",
                "target of 0.088 mg/cm**2 thickness was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two types of detector system were",
                "employed at different angular range-",
                "delta-E-E telescopes and combination of E-E detectors",
                "for kinematical coincidence measurements.",
                "Two delta-E-E telescopes consisting of 40-70 mum as",
                "delta-E and 500 mum-1 mm E counters were located on the",
                "both sides of the beam.",
                "The scattering events at the medium angles(Ang(lab)=",
                " 20-28 degree) were measured by means kinematical",
                "coincidence method-Two silicon detectors of 20*20-mm",
                "size and 1 mm thickness each were used for registration",
                "of O-16nuclei and one silicon detector of 20*20-mm size",
                "and 380 mum thickness was located on the other side for",
                "registration of the Ca-40 nuclei"
              ]
            }
          ],
